I have been finding it difficult to sleep for a long time. Kindly let me know how I can sleep more. Also let me know the advantages of sleeping. I am a 50- year old business man. Kayode (by SMS)  Apart from making sure that your bed and beddings are in good conditions, it is also important for you to decrease your bedroom light, create a bedtime routine and limit phone and TV use in bed. In addition, you need to decrease your caffeine intake and increase exercises. All these should be done with the belief that your Blood Pressure and other vital signs have been checked to be normal. It has been confirmed that getting more sleep is healthy. In addition to giving an individual more energy during the day, good sleep (approximately 7 hours per day) also makes the person more alert and improves the mood. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…Provost of Federal College  Provost of Federal College Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…Provost of Federal College  Provost of Federal College ORITAMEFA BAPTIST MODEL SCHOOLS, (OBMS), IBADAN 
